  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Partnership for Building  Resilience for Urban Informal Food Markets in Harare</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, Oxfam also supported rehabilitation of markets to make them COVID -19 safe environments. United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) intends to expand ongoing interventions in Mbare, and the project aims to promote hygiene, protect livelihoods through setting up green enterprises for Asher, bio -digester, waste transfer station and material recovery facility and building resilience to future shocks. The project will ensure operationalization of green solutions and that the new markets remain COVID -19 safe markets, have improved hygiene enablers for increased livelihood participation, solid waste management and economic empowerment in the target communities. The project will support the other Mbare markets to be green, COVID -compliant, gender safe and aligned with City of Harare masterplan for market stalls. Oxfam will support establishment of a gender and risk analysis on COVID -19 to assess the impacts on different groups of people at water points to develop and implement mitigation measures for prevention of sexual exploitation and abuse. Oxfam will support coordination and decision making for gender inclusivity at local and national level and mainstreaming Gender Based Violence (GBV) during radio talk shows and loud hailers during hygiene promotion. The project will run for a period of 6 months up to 30 June 2022</narrative>
  </description>
